
## Kuřimská Nová Ves

Kuřimská Nová Ves is a village and municipality (obec) in Brno-Country District in the South Moravian Region of the Czech Republic.
The municipality covers an area of 4.87 square kilometres (1.88 sq mi), and has a population of 133 (as at 2 October 2006).
Kuřimská Nová Ves lies approximately 29 kilometres (18 mi) north-west of Brno and 158 km (98 mi) south-east of Prague.

